# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0
# Adjustfile — Drift-tolerance contract for IDApTIK
# Author: IDApTIK contributors
#
# Cumulative-drift catchment: tolerance bands + corrective actions.
# Authority: advisory (Yard) — continue-with-warnings; auto_fix where deterministic.
# Run with: adjust check

@abstract:
Drift tolerances and corrective actions for IDApTIK. Unlike MUST (hard gate),
ADJUST tracks cumulative drift against tolerance bands and proposes corrective
actions. Advisory — it warns and trends, it does not block.
@end

## Architecture Drift

### core-engine-isolation
- description: crates/idaptik-core must not depend on a rendering engine
- tolerance: 0 references to bevy/fyrox in idaptik-core's dependencies
- corrective: Move rendering-coupled code into the frontend crates (ADR-0003)
- severity: advisory

### determinism-drift
- description: Gameplay-truth sim stays deterministic (replay/export depend on it)
- tolerance: 0 unseeded RNG / wall-clock reads in crates/idaptik-core sim paths
- corrective: Route randomness through the seeded scenario RNG (ADR-0004)
- severity: advisory

## Documentation Drift

### state-freshness
- description: STATE.a2ml should track the real phase and component status
- tolerance: STATE.a2ml last-updated within one milestone of HEAD
- corrective: Refresh .machine_readable/6a2/STATE.a2ml from README.md + docs/adr/
- severity: advisory

### adr-coverage
- description: Settled decisions are recorded as ADRs rather than asserted in prose
- tolerance: Every "Still open" item in README either open or backed by an ADR
- corrective: Write the ADR under docs/adr/ when a decision lands
- severity: advisory

## Licensing Drift

### license-layer-consistency
- description: Engine sources are AGPL-3.0-or-later; content assets are CC-BY-SA-4.0
- tolerance: 0 files whose SPDX header crosses the engine/content layer boundary
- corrective: Correct the SPDX header to match the file's layer
- severity: advisory

### spdx-header-consistency
- description: All committed source/metadata files carry an SPDX header
- tolerance: 0 source files missing SPDX-License-Identifier
- corrective: Add the correct SPDX header for the file's layer
- severity: advisory

## Toolchain Drift

### pin-sync
- description: mise.toml and rust-toolchain.toml pins stay consistent with CI
- tolerance: CI toolchain versions match the committed pins
- corrective: Reconcile .github/workflows with mise.toml / rust-toolchain.toml
- severity: advisory
